column1: The Crow family wishes you a speedy recovery. Even mild COVID-19 symptoms can be concerning and we thank you for leading by example and quarantining yourself during this time. https://t.co/ZWZnOE9I4X

COVID-19 is one of the greatest challenges we’ve ever faced. I’m grateful for the dedication of frontline healthcare workers like Reps. @YadiraCaraveo & @Kyle_Mullica. Thanks for sharing your experiences with me. Together we can fight to get our communities the resources we need. https://t.co/1edcB8iX44

Thanks to @JEWISHco for inviting me to the 2020 Candidates Forum. We had a great convo about issues that matter most to Coloradans -- from healthcare & COVID-19 relief to ensuring our elections are safe & secure. Make your voice heard this election & vote! https://t.co/vB2QiTsMZh

I’ve been hearing from Coloradans in CD6 about how COVID-19 has upended their lives. That’s why I’m fighting in Congress for more support for our small businesses funding for testing and contact tracing and PPE for our first responders. https://t.co/sAAuk9Okpi

Jared Kushner has been going on TV to vouch for Trump’s COVID-19 response but I don’t know under what scenario Kushner has credibility left in this debate.  We need a President who won't downplay the facts & strong leadership in the White House to guide us out of this crisis. https://t.co/sfD5VUmEyk
Across Colorado kids are going back to school. But this administration's failure to address COVID-19 is putting kids and teachers at risk.

COVID-19 has delivered a massive blow to our small business community. This National Black Business Month show your support for Black-owned businesses in CD6 by visiting one (or a few!) of the great establishments on this list compiled by 303 Magazine.  https://t.co/vSFxFICTYH

It is time that we had a fighter in the Senate who will support Coloradans - not play politics with people’s lives.  Thanks to @Hickenlooper for inviting me to join today's roundtable on COVID-19 relief. I know John won't let politics stand in the way of helping Colorado. https://t.co/Qc1jSz8gRR

We need to rapidly build up our public health workforce. The first step is making sure we have the people in place to address this crisis. I’m proud to introduce a bill to create a Health Force to train and employ Americans to respond to COVID-19.  https://t.co/UqTE1fYWoK https://t.co/Z8xQp5MDaL

Last week Deserai and I got to touch base with some of our campaign's great volunteer leaders. Thanks to them our COVID-19 community check-in program has reached out to more than 60000 people across CD6 to help them find the resources they may need during these tough times. https://t.co/Lp2rLcKoMb

May is Mental Health Awareness Month. Social distancing and the threat of COVID-19 can take a big toll on mental health.  If you're struggling during this tough time know that you are not alone.   Find more mental healthcare resources here:   https://t.co/MvU0v8OLhl https://t.co/JLmyjC8prM

Proud to join @RobinLynneKelly @BLeeForCongress @AyannaPressley and @KarenBassTweets in calling on the CDC to release racial & ethnic data on COVID-19. The virus disproportionately affects communities of color and we must study these inequities if we hope to address them.

COVID-19 has shown us we must continue to grow our public health workforce and improve America's readiness for pandemics. That's why I'm proud to introduce a loan repayment program for the public health workers serving our communities.  https://t.co/RhF9jkR86J https://t.co/U1SjciMd9d

When COVID-19 hit our community we knew we couldn't run a typical campaign. So we launched our community check-in program and Team Crow volunteers have reached out to 30000+ neighbors to make sure they are doing okay. Check out some of the responses we've gotten👇 https://t.co/5bdr0KG9OM
ICYMI: Crow and Coffman: Coronavirus stimulus dollars must also help state and city governments  https://t.co/VkpSYcfTQd https://t.co/Eavjf3brmx
Starting at 12:50pm the U.S. Air Force Thunderbirds will be flying over the Front Range to salute our brave COVID-19 frontline responders. You can find their path here 👇 https://t.co/ME79DJaW20

Thank you to the @CWAunion members who continue to help us get through this difficult time. We need to make sure that our essential workers are protected and their voices heard as our country responds to the Coronavirus. https://t.co/EVx2D3bcGr

As our community comes together to respond to this public health crisis our team complied a list of resources for up-to-date accurate information on COVID-19. Check it out here:   https://t.co/pAziJWG8ge https://t.co/jDETmx7Jki

For those at risk for domestic violence sheltering in place during the Coronavirus can mean danger. While we're fighting this pandemic we need to also provide support and resources to those at risk.  https://t.co/qOWTVuNAJg https://t.co/RF7I35zxNE

As pleas from health care workers for more personal protective equipment grow and hospitals expect a surge of ill COVID-19 patients... Jason Crow is pushing a bill that would compel President Donald Trump to use his authority to acquire more supplies.   https://t.co/S7ecYv8LIp https://t.co/NNOcTGm9Pn

24 hours ago I flew into Washington to vote on the CARES Act to provide economic and public health aid on response to the COVID-19 crisis. Now with hand sanitizer and Clorox wipes at the ready I’m taking the red eye back to Colorado. https://t.co/5qfFkka6Ne

Are you a retired healthcare professional or healthcare student? Colorado needs your help as we fight the Coronavirus. Visit https://t.co/jgXUEWtPM1 to volunteer to help at a care facility in your area.
ICYMI: Colorado Congressman Jason Crow Introduces Bill To Help Small Businesses Survive During Coronavirus  https://t.co/CMZ4HKbOT8 https://t.co/HFSyT9o6oC

Thank you to the @coloradodems @arapahoedems @AdamsCountyDem and Douglas County Democratic Party for their tireless work to adapt our convention process in the midst of COVID-19. Practicing responsible social distancing is how we keep Coloradans safe.  https://t.co/2vDifmHAfj

With labs in Aurora Greffex is developing a vaccine for COVID-19. Their work is crucial in helping find a solution to this crisis. We are all grateful for the scientists technicians & healthcare workers who stand on the frontlines of the Coronavirus.   https://t.co/TfHf6lDz4I

Concerned about coronavirus? UCHealth is leading the way by providing safe and affordable 24/7 care with their Virtual Urgent Care services. The service is available for all Coloradans not just UCHealth patients.  https://t.co/figVVGfwHN

With the news of Coronavirus cases in Colorado make sure to wash your hands cover sneezes and coughs and stay home if you're sick (except for medical care). Click on the link to learn more:   https://t.co/3BiKijN00J https://t.co/3qjkYeb25p
